# ── Now Playing (vinyl player) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Apple Music has no public web API for "what I'm playing", so the player reads
# your plays from Last.fm. Apple Music → Last.fm needs a scrobbler app, e.g.:
#   • iPhone/iPad: Marvis Pro, or Cider
#   • Mac: NepTunes, or Cider
# Once your Apple Music plays scrobble to Last.fm, fill these in:
#
# 1. Your Last.fm username (public)
NEXT_PUBLIC_LASTFM_USER=
# 2. A free Last.fm API key → https://www.last.fm/api/account/create
#    (read-only public app key; safe to expose in a client app)
NEXT_PUBLIC_LASTFM_API_KEY=

# ── Song suggestions → email ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. With a Web3Forms key, the "Suggest a song" box emails you directly.
# Without it, the box falls back to opening the visitor's email client.
# Free key → https://web3forms.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_KEY=

# To use: copy this file to ".env.local", fill the values, and restart the dev
# server (npm run dev). .env.local is gitignored, so your keys stay local.
